title._content: Cecile Lorraine, American soprano, as Marguerite in Faust (or as Leonora in La Forza del destino), 1901 / photographer Grouzelle Studios

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales
tag.author: 29454428@N08

description._content: Note: In 1901, two opera companies sang 169 performances over 10 months in Sydney, a city of half a million people, as part of the Federation celebrations. Cecile Lorraine was one of the sopranos. Format: Paris Panel Notes: Find more detailed information about this photograph: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=890119 Search for more great images in the State Library's collections: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/search/SimpleSearch.aspx From the collection of the State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au
